  m_Name: Flexor_carpi_radialis_muscle.L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Flexor_carpi_radialis_muscle.L
  partName: Flexor carpi radialis muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left flexor carpi radialis muscle is located along the medial aspect of the
    canine forearm and functions primarily to flex the carpal joint. Originating
    from the medial humerus and inserting onto the metacarpal bones, this muscle
    contributes to controlled wrist flexion during locomotion and weight-bearing
    activities.
  - It also assists in stabilizing the carpus while maintaining proper paw positioning
    during movement. Coordinated action with surrounding flexor muscles improves
    balance, stride efficiency, and shock absorption when the forelimb contacts the
    ground. Proper muscular function is essential for smooth forelimb mechanics.
